ref: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.394, p.189 (1983)
title: Identification of quasimolecular resonances in low energy alpha-40Ca scattering and effects of compound nucleus excitation.

x4freetext: Identification of quasimolecular resonances in low
energy alpha-40Ca scattering and effects of compound
nucleus excitation.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.394, p.189 (1983)

x4freetext: The target consisted of about 5 ug/cm2 metallic Ca
evaporated onto a 6 ug/cm2 carbon backing. An
additional gold layer (1 ug/cm2) prevented the target
from oxidation and served for a precise determination
of the absolute cross section by comparing with
Rutherford scattering.
